x>0
\frac{d}{dx}\ln |x|=\frac{d}{dx}\ln x=\frac{1}{x}
x<0
\frac{d}{dx}\ln |x|=\frac{d}{dx}\ln (-x)=\frac{1}{-x}\times \frac{d}{dx}(-x)=\frac{1}{-x}\times (-1)=\frac{1}{x} 
\int \frac{1}{x}dx=\ln |x|+C,  x \ne 0
x
|x|=\sqrt{x^2}
\bigl(\ln|x|\bigr)'=\bigr(\ln(\sqrt{x^2})\bigr)'=\dfrac{1}{\sqrt{x^2}}\dfrac{1}{2\sqrt{x^2}}\cdot2x=\dfrac{x}{|x|^2}=\dfrac{x}{x^2}=\dfrac{1}{x}
